The paper deals with optimization problems related to multi-user interference channels, which are typically studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of beamforming techniques and single-user detection also suggests the possibility of the paper being related to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also be relevant to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
